English Sentences: I have compared thee, O my love, to a company of horses in Pharaoh's chariots.

English Sentences: Thy cheeks are comely with rows of jewels, thy neck with chains of gold.

English Sentences: Behold, thou art fair, my love; behold, thou art fair; thou hast doves' eyes.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ta siiqee, neeni aiba lo77ai! Neeni aiba lo77ai! Ne aifeti haraphphiyaa aifiyaadan lo77oosona" yaagiis. Geela7iyaa:

English Sentences: As the lily among thorns, so is my love among the daughters.

English Sentences: As the apple tree among the trees of the wood, so is my beloved among the sons. I sat down under his shadow with great delight, and his fruit was sweet to my taste.

English Sentences: The voice of my beloved! behold, he cometh leaping upon the mountains, skipping upon the hills.

English Sentences: Until the day break, and the shadows flee away, I will get me to the mountain of myrrh, and to the hill of frankincense.

Ta binnaanaikka qamma diifiyan narkkakkiis yaagees.
